import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='cx', y='cy')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of longitude and latitude coordinates in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='cx', ascending=False)
    sns.barplot(x='name', y='cx', data=data)
    plt.axhline(y=data['cx'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max Longitude: {data['cx'].max():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.spatial.distance import pdist, squareform

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate the pairwise distance between the locations
    dist = pd.DataFrame(squareform(pdist(data[['cx', 'cy']])), columns=data['name'], index=data['name'])
    
    # Generate the heatmap
    sns.heatmap(dist, cmap='YlGnBu', annot=True, fmt='.2f')
    
    # Set the chart title
    plt.title('What is the average distance between the locations in London?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.spatial.distance import pdist, squareform

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate the pairwise distance between the locations
    dist = pd.DataFrame(squareform(pdist(data[['cx', 'cy']])), columns=data['name'], index=data['name'])
    
    # Generate the heatmap
    sns.heatmap(dist, cmap='YlGnBu', annot=True, fmt='.2f')
    
    # Set the chart title
    plt.title('What is the average distance between the locations in London?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt
